---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Magic Chef Oven Repair | Southern California | Compact, Apartment, ADU";
const description = "Magic Chef oven repair across SoCal, 20\"/24\" compact gas + electric, apartment ovens, microwave ovens. Multi-family fleet + ADU specialty. $89 dx.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/magic-chef-oven-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What sizes does Magic Chef make, is it full-size 30\" oven or compact?",
    a: "Current MCA-era Magic Chef is compact + apartment-sized, not full-size. Range + oven sizes: <b>20\" compact range</b> with integrated oven (the smallest residential kitchen range commonly sold in the US, designed for apartment galley kitchens), <b>24\" apartment-size range</b> with integrated oven (fits slightly wider apartment kitchen cutouts + ADU kitchens), and <b>countertop + built-in microwave ovens</b> in various compact formats. Magic Chef no longer manufactures 30\" full-size ranges, 30\" wall ovens, or full-capacity combination ovens, those are GE, Samsung, LG, Whirlpool, Frigidaire territory. If you have what you think is a 30\" Magic Chef, verify the model number, you may have an older 1970s-1990s unit from the pre-MCA era (American Stove Co / Maytag-era), which has different service considerations including parts-availability limitations."
  },
  {
    q: "Our apartment building has Magic Chef ranges in 12 units, do you do fleet service?",
    a: "Yes, multi-family property-manager fleet service is a significant part of our Magic Chef work. Fleet approach differs from individual-household service: <b>volume pricing</b> below standard $89 per-call when dispatched across multiple units in one building or portfolio; <b>dispatch efficiency</b>, triage all reported failures in one visit rather than separate calls per unit; <b>parts consolidation</b>, common Magic Chef components travel on truck for fleet clients; <b>honest repair-vs-replace triage</b>, frank economic guidance on which failing units justify repair and which should cycle into replacement budget. Our LA fleet concentrations include Silver Lake, East Hollywood, Koreatown, Westlake, Panorama City multi-family rental buildings. Initial fleet-service setup requires conversation about property portfolio + typical call volume + common Magic Chef models. Contact (424) 325-0520."
  },
  {
    q: "Magic Chef compact oven won't heat, what's the usual failure?",
    a: "Most common Magic Chef oven failures in order: (1) <b>Bake element failure</b>, element continuity fails, bake mode stops heating, $155-$235 replacement including the lower parts pricing for compact-size elements. #1 call. (2) <b>Gas igniter</b> on gas-fuel Magic Chef ranges, igniter glows but can't trigger the gas valve, $175-$265 on the compact-range gas igniter spec. Most common gas-specific complaint. (3) <b>Thermal sensor / thermostat drift</b>, erratic temperature or runaway, $115-$185 replacement. (4) <b>Door hinge or gasket wear</b>, Magic Chef compact oven doors are lighter than full-size, but rental-unit use patterns (frequent opening, kids bumping door, cleaning contact) cause hinge + gasket wear patterns at 4-7 year service-life on fleet units. Hinge pair $185-$285, gasket $115-$175. (5) <b>Control board</b> at 8-12 years on mid-tier Magic Chef ovens, $245-$345. Simpler control architecture than mainstream brands keeps board pricing low."
  },
  {
    q: "Does Magic Chef do microwave oven service too?",
    a: "Yes, Magic Chef microwave ovens are a distinct service category we cover. Product format: countertop compact microwaves (small kitchen + RV use) and over-the-range microwave-oven combinations (integrated into the kitchen range above the stove). Service economics on Magic Chef microwaves favor component-level repair for 5-8 year units, replacement for 10+ year units given the low retail cost. Common Magic Chef microwave service: magnetron $185-$285 (compact magnetron pricing); door switch set $95-$145; keypad / membrane $145-$215; turntable motor $85-$125; control board $185-$265. Magic Chef microwave-oven-specific safety protocol: we discharge the high-voltage capacitor before any internal service, same as all microwave brands, general-handyman service sometimes skips this step, which creates serious electrical hazards."
  },
  {
    q: "Is it worth repairing a 5-year-old Magic Chef compact range?",
    a: "Usually yes on single-component failures; often no on multi-component failures. Magic Chef compact ranges retail at $400-$800 depending on size + fuel type. Service economics: $89 diagnostic + $155-$345 typical component replacement. <b>Clear repair</b>: bake element, gas igniter, thermostat, door gasket at 5-year age, repair $245-$435 total on a $500-$800 replacement cost. Repair favorable. <b>Borderline</b>: control board at $245-$345 on a $500 compact range, repair-to-value ratio approaches 50%. Property-manager fleet often repairs anyway given replacement logistics (remove old + transport + dispose + buy new + install) add $150-$300 beyond retail. Individual household might lean replacement. <b>Replacement favorable</b>: multiple simultaneous failures, or 10+ year units showing additional near-term failure risk. We quote honestly at diagnostic and flag trade-offs when repair total approaches replacement cost."
  },
  {
    q: "Magic Chef 20\" range for ADU, do you install new units too?",
    a: "We focus on service + repair rather than new installation. Installation services are typically handled by the appliance retailer or a general contractor as part of the overall ADU kitchen project. What we do provide: <b>post-installation commissioning</b> (verify the new Magic Chef unit is operating to spec, calibrate oven temperature, confirm gas line pressure for gas models, check electrical circuit load for electric models) at standard diagnostic rate if needed; <b>troubleshooting</b> if a newly installed Magic Chef has issues immediately after installation. We do not resell appliances. For new Magic Chef purchase, most LA appliance retailers carry the brand, Sears parts & service pre-bankruptcy was a common channel, now replaced by Amazon + Home Depot + Lowe's + independent appliance retailers + direct from MCA."
  },
  {
    q: "Magic Chef vs Kenmore vs Amana, which is the 'right' value-tier choice?",
    a: "Different products for different use cases, not a direct like-for-like comparison. <b>Magic Chef</b> (this page), compact + apartment-size specialization, MCA Corporation 2001+, strongest fit for apartment + ADU + small-kitchen installations. <b>Kenmore</b>, retailer brand, NOT a manufacturer, units built by various OEMs (Whirlpool, Frigidaire, LG, Samsung, GE), model-number prefix decoding identifies which OEM. More product flexibility across sizes but service complexity depends on OEM. See <a href='/brands/kenmore-oven-repair/'>Kenmore oven repair</a>. <b>Amana</b>, Whirlpool-owned value-tier, typically full-size ranges + refrigerators at budget pricing, not compact. See <a href='/brands/amana-range-repair/'>Amana range repair</a>. Choice drivers: Magic Chef for compact fit; Kenmore for OEM-specific equivalence at varied sizes; Amana for full-size budget mainstream."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does Magic Chef oven repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair (individual household). Multi-family fleet: ask about volume pricing. Common Magic Chef oven service bands: thermal fuse $85-$135; thermostat / thermal sensor $115-$185; bake element $155-$235; broil element $165-$245; gas oven igniter $175-$265; gas valve $245-$365; door hinge pair $185-$285; door gasket $115-$175; inner door glass $195-$285; control board $245-$345; keypad / selector switch $145-$215; oven light $65-$105. Microwave-oven add: magnetron $185-$285; door switch set $95-$145; keypad $145-$215; turntable motor $85-$125. Magic Chef pricing runs 25-40% below mainstream-brand equivalent service given compact-parts economics and simpler control architecture. Property-manager fleet pricing further reduced on volume dispatch."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, Magic Chef Oven Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL, "priceRange": "$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "Magic Chef Oven Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Magic Chef oven repair across LA, 20\"/24\" compact gas + electric ranges with integrated ovens, compact built-in ovens, countertop + over-the-range microwave ovens. MCA Corporation 2001+ compact/apartment-size specialization. Multi-family property-manager fleet service + ADU + rental-unit concentration. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair; fleet volume pricing available.",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Magic Chef", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/magic-chef/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Magic Chef Oven Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>Magic Chef oven service? Same-day across LA:</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › <a href="/brands/magic-chef/">Magic Chef</a> › Oven Repair</div>
    <h1>Magic Chef Oven Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">Magic Chef ovens in LA kitchens mean one of three things: <b>apartment-building rental unit</b> (20\" compact range in a multi-family property), <b>ADU conversion</b> (24\" apartment-size range in a converted garage or backyard unit), or <b>urban condo + small-kitchen household</b> where compact appliances fit tight kitchen footprints. 201 GSC impressions on Magic Chef oven queries in our 3-month observation reflect genuine LA demand, and our service approach reflects Magic Chef's actual market position as value-tier compact, not marketing-polished premium. Our service covers <b>20\"/24\" compact gas + electric ranges with integrated ovens</b>, <b>compact built-in ovens</b>, <b>microwave ovens</b> (countertop + over-the-range combination formats), and <b>multi-family property-manager fleet service</b> with volume pricing below individual-household rate. Same-day dispatch. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>201 imp, strongest Value-tier signal</b> in LA oven GSC</li>
      <li><b>Multi-family fleet service</b>, property-manager volume pricing</li>
      <li><b>ADU + rental-unit specialty</b>, no LA competitor targets this segment</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Magic Chef in LA, compact + apartment specialization, honest value-tier framing</h2>
    <p>Magic Chef oven service concentrates in installations where compact appliance sizes are requirements, not preferences. 20\" ranges fit apartment galley kitchens where 30\" full-size would literally not physically install. 24\" apartment-size ranges fit ADU kitchenettes + older small-home cutouts. Compact microwave ovens fit tight countertop space. This isn't the target audience being sold on features + brand prestige, it's the target audience being sold on fit + price + reliability-for-the-use-case.</p>
    <p>LA's multi-family housing stock skews heavily toward older buildings (1920s Spanish Colonial revival, 1940s Mid-Century, 1960s dingbat, 1970s Pomeroy-style courtyard) with kitchen footprints that were never designed for 30\" modern ranges. Property managers replacing failed units across these buildings default to Magic Chef, Summit, Avanti, or Danby, compact-specialty brands, because that's what fits. Magic Chef is the scale leader in this segment by GSC signal.</p>
    <p>Our approach: service Magic Chef units honestly for what they are, without pretending they're something else. The compact range in a Silver Lake 1920s bungalow rental costs $550 new; a $300 repair on a 6-year-old unit keeps it running another 5 years at real economic value for the property manager. The 30\" GE range in a Brentwood remodel costs $2,800 new; different product, different service expectations, different repair economics.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Magic Chef oven failures our techs see most often in LA</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Bake element failure (#1 Magic Chef oven call)</h3><p>Element continuity fails, bake mode stops heating. Swap $155-$235, lower pricing than mainstream given compact-element spec.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Gas oven igniter (gas-fuel models)</h3><p>Igniter glows but can't trigger gas valve. #1 gas-specific Magic Chef complaint. Swap $175-$265 on compact-range igniter spec.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Thermostat / thermal sensor drift</h3><p>Erratic temperature or runaway. Magic Chef ovens use simpler thermostat architecture than full-size mainstream, $115-$185 replacement, cheaper than mainstream thermal sensors.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Door hinge + gasket wear (rental-unit use patterns)</h3><p>4-7 year service-life on fleet units reflects high-frequency rental-unit use. Hinge pair $185-$285; gasket $115-$175.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Control board at 8-12 years (mid-tier)</h3><p>Simpler control architecture means cheaper replacement. $245-$345 on Magic Chef mid-tier ovens. Entry-tier often has no electronic control board, knobs + mechanical thermostat.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Microwave oven magnetron + door switch</h3><p>Magic Chef microwave-oven service. Magnetron $185-$285; door switch set $95-$145; keypad $145-$215. HV capacitor discharge safety protocol on every microwave service.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Magic Chef oven product lines we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>20\" compact range (apartment)</h3><p>Smallest residential range commonly sold in US. Apartment galley-kitchen + 1920s-1970s building stock fit. Gas or electric fuel. Integrated compact oven below 4-burner cooktop.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>24\" apartment-size range (ADU)</h3><p>Slightly wider than 20\" for ADU + smaller mid-size apartment kitchens. Integrated oven, 4-burner cooktop. Most common Magic Chef size in our LA fleet service.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Compact built-in ovens</h3><p>Wall-mounted built-in ovens in compact 24\" size. Less common than range-integrated oven format, but available for specific kitchen layouts.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Countertop microwave ovens</h3><p>Compact countertop microwaves for small kitchen, RV, tiny-home, dorm installations. Low-wattage + compact-form-factor magnetron architecture.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Over-the-range microwave combinations</h3><p>Microwave mounted above range cooktop, integrated into compact-kitchen layouts. Combination service covers both microwave section + any integrated oven venting.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Fleet-service common-parts stock</h3><p>Multi-family property-manager fleet clients get priority stocking of common Magic Chef oven components on our service trucks, bake elements, gas igniters, thermostats, door gaskets.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>What Magic Chef oven repair costs in LA</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
      <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Residential diagnostic (individual)</td><td>$89</td><td>Waived with repair</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Fleet-service dispatch</td><td>Volume quote</td><td>Property-manager accounts</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Thermal fuse</td><td>$85 – $135</td><td>Safety</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Thermostat / thermal sensor</td><td>$115 – $185</td><td>Simpler than mainstream</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Bake element (compact)</td><td>$155 – $235</td><td>Compact-element pricing</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Broil element (compact)</td><td>$165 – $245</td><td>Top cavity</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Gas oven igniter (compact)</td><td>$175 – $265</td><td>Compact-range spec</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Gas valve</td><td>$245 – $365</td><td>Secondary after igniter</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Door hinge pair</td><td>$185 – $285</td><td>Compact hinges</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Door gasket</td><td>$115 – $175</td><td>Heat-seal</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Inner door glass</td><td>$195 – $285</td><td>Compact pane</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Control board (mid-tier)</td><td>$245 – $345</td><td>Simpler architecture</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Keypad / selector switch</td><td>$145 – $215</td><td>Touch or physical</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Oven light</td><td>$65 – $105</td><td>High-temp bulb</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Microwave magnetron</td><td>$185 – $285</td><td>Compact magnetron</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Microwave door switch set</td><td>$95 – $145</td><td>3-switch standard</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Microwave keypad</td><td>$145 – $215</td><td>Membrane + controller</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Microwave turntable motor</td><td>$85 – $125</td><td>Glass-plate rotation</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="small">Magic Chef pricing runs 25-40% below mainstream-brand equivalent (GE, Samsung, LG) given compact-parts economics + simpler control architecture. Multi-family fleet accounts get further volume-based reduction.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>LA service areas, Magic Chef oven concentrations</h2>
    <div class="area-grid">
      <div><h4>Silver Lake + East Hollywood</h4><p>Silver Lake · Echo Park · East Hollywood · Los Feliz · Atwater, multi-family 1920s-1970s stock</p></div>
      <div><h4>Koreatown + Westlake</h4><p>Koreatown · Westlake · MacArthur Park · Pico-Union · Wilshire Center</p></div>
      <div><h4>Mid-Wilshire apartment buildings</h4><p>Mid-Wilshire · Miracle Mile · Park La Brea · Hancock Park apartments</p></div>
      <div><h4>Panorama City + Van Nuys</h4><p>Panorama City · Van Nuys · North Hollywood · North Hills</p></div>
      <div><h4>DTLA condo + loft</h4><p>Downtown · Arts District · South Park · Historic Core · Little Tokyo</p></div>
      <div><h4>ADU conversions citywide</h4><p>Backyard ADU + garage conversion kitchens across LA basin</p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Related Magic Chef and compact-appliance pages</h2>
    <ul class="related-links">
      <li><a href="/brands/magic-chef/">Magic Chef brand hub (all categories) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/magic-chef-stove-repair/">Magic Chef stove / range repair →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/haier-oven-repair/">Haier oven repair (compact peer, urban apartments) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/kenmore-oven-repair/">Kenmore oven repair (multi-OEM peer) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/services/oven-repair/">Oven repair service hub →</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Magic Chef oven repair, frequently asked</h2>
    {faqs.map(f => (<details class="faq"><summary>{f.q}</summary><p set:html={f.a}></p></details>))}
  </div></section>

  <section id="book" class="cta-bottom"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Magic Chef oven service? Call the branch closest to your property.</h2>
    <p>Same-day appliance repair in LA, Orange County, Ventura County. Individual-household $89. Multi-family property managers, ask about fleet pricing.</p>
  </div></section>
  <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="float-call" aria-label="Call now">☎ Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
</Layout>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
  body { color: var(--text); } .wrap { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; } .wrap.narrow { max-width: 820px; }
  h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; line-height: 1.15; margin: 12px 0 20px; color: var(--black); }
  h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 0 0 16px; color: var(--black); }
  h3 { font-size: 1.2rem; margin: 0 0 10px; color: var(--black); }
  h4 { font-size: 1.02rem; margin: 0 0 6px; color: var(--black); }
  p { line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .call-banner { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 10px 0; }
  .call-banner .wrap { display:flex; gap: 14px; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .call-banner .phone-lg { color:#fff; font-weight: 800; text-decoration: underline; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .hero { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 42px 0 56px; } .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .hero .lede { font-size: 1.06rem; color: #d7d7d7; max-width: 680px; }
  .hero .crumb { color: #9a9a9a; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 6px; } .hero .crumb a { color: #c9c9c9; text-decoration: none; }
  .hero-cta { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 18px 0 24px; }
  .btn { display: inline-block; padding: 12px 20px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--red); color: #fff; } .btn-ghost { background: transparent; color: #fff; border: 1px solid #fff; }
  .hero-facts { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; color: #c9c9c9; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .hero-facts li { padding: 6px 0; border-top: 1px solid #222; } .hero-facts li:first-child { border-top: 0; }
  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 0; }
  .trust-bar .wrap { display: flex; gap: 28px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .section { padding: 56px 0; } .section.alt { background: var(--gray); }
  .model-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 24px; }
  .model-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px; border-radius: 6px; }
  .section.alt .model-card { background: #fff; }
  .fail-block { background: #fff; border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px 22px; margin: 16px 0; }
  .price-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 14px; background: #fff; }
  .price-table th, .price-table td { text-align: left; padding: 11px 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .price-table th { background: var(--black); color: #fff; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .small { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.92rem; margin-top: 12px; }
  .area-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; }
  .area-grid > div { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 16px; border-radius: 6px; }
  .related-links { list-style: none; padding: 0; } .related-links li { padding: 10px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .related-links a { color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; } .related-links a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .faq { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 12px 16px; margin-bottom: 8px; border-radius: 4px; }
  .faq summary { font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; padding: 4px 0; } .faq p { margin: 8px 0 0; }
  .cta-bottom { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 48px 0; } .cta-bottom h2 { color: #fff; } .cta-bottom p { color: #c9c9c9; }
  .float-call { position: fixed; bottom: 18px; right: 18px; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 18px; border-radius: 40px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; box-shadow: 0 6px 18px rgba(0,0,0,0.28); z-index: 50; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  @media (max-width: 820px) { h1 { font-size: 1.9rem; } h2 { font-size: 1.45rem; } .float-call { padding: 11px 14px; font-size: 0.88rem; } .trust-bar .wrap { gap: 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; } }
</style>
